you re looking at me like i live here and i don t events at stanford you re looking at me like i live here and i don t facebook twitter email print add to calendar in this film directed by scott kirschenbaum a woman in the middle stages of alzheimer's disease seeks acceptance among fellow residents at the traditions alzheimer's & other dementia care unit as she fights against the forces of a past she cannot remember wandering day after day on a soul searching odyssey through her alzheimer's care unit confined by the limits of her physical boundaries she scavenges for reminders of her old identity in the outside world the center on longevity will sponsor a screening of this film followed by a panel discussion on february 16 panelists scott kirschenbaum filmmaker dr victor henderson professor of health research and policy and of neurology and neurological sciences esther wilson arias alzheimer's association of northern california dr yoshiko matsumoto professor of japanese language and linguistics when thursday february 16 2012 5 30 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where cubberley auditorium map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends members tags other environment humanities health wellness public service sponsor stanford center on longevity contact 736.8643 rlonhart stanford edu admission open to the public free of charge permalink http events stanford edu events 310 31063 more info last modified february 13 2012
